			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Bring:
<br />
 - 1 rogue
<br />
 - necro nonkos to chardok
<br />
 - someone to loot whatever it is you're getting
<br />

<br />
Goto target. Root one of the mobs in the target's assist range. This will cause the target any any other mobs in assist range to aggro. This is known as indirect aggro.
<br />

<br />
You can train those aggro mobs past anything else you want in the zone, nothing else will add unless you gain direct aggro on those mobs in the train by casting on them, meleeing them, pet attacking them, or them catching you.
<br />

<br />
Example: I bring the overking to the zone as follows: 
<br />
 - rogue open door 1
<br />
 - rogue open door2 and wait by door2.
<br />
 - Overking in pit with 2 adds. Tell rogue to open door2 and then door1.
<br />
 - Root one of the two adds. Run away with Overking and 1 add. The Overking is a wizard.
<br />
 - Take add off somewhere and either solo it down or root it around green/lightblue mobs
<br />
 - Return towards overking (who has been chilling casting okeils on sarnaks) until he charges me again, still from indirect aggro
<br />
 - Walk with king to front. Always move around corners so he will stop casting annoying useless spells and just walk his ass up to the front.
<br />
 - Have my "click the nightmare hide to stop being blind" hotkey ready.
<br />
 - Summonkite the king at the front. Lifeburn him at 30% since gating wizard named mobs could suck.
<br />

<br />
Normally the cleric that's there for their epic piece will give me a heal or two and the rogue will poke at him some, but it's not needed at all. Make certain your resists are acceptable, you're going to be nuked a lot, and his cute little ae is annoying as well.
<br />

<br />
The faction hit for the king, queen, or prince are no more than killing any other trash mob in the zone; I've farmed nameds there including the royalty for half a year and I'm still as warmly as when I started.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Indirect aggro is a very strong tool for pulling in a zone where you are not kos. Would have been nice in velious if the mobs there didn't resist everything.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=894132" target="_blank" class="postlink">Gnemesis</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.agonyguild.net" target="_blank" class="postlink">Agony</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.vazaelle.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Vazaelle</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
